How to Record Your Screen with VLC [For Fun]The ever versatile VLC can do a lot of things. Screen recording is one of them. https://itsfoss.com/vlc-record-screen/ 650a776dbb002c9598310f15VLCSreenath Wed, 11 Oct 2023 02:58:43 GMT <img src="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/10/record-screen-with-vlc.png" alt="How to Record Your Screen with VLC [For Fun]"><p> VLC is more than just a video player. It&#39;s a versatile video tool with so many features that a normal user could never know them.</p><p> You can <a href="https://itsfoss.com/download-youtube-videos-vlc/">download YouTube videos with VLC</a> or even trim videos with it.</p><p> Another such unusual use of VLC is for screen recording.</p><p> <strong>I still recommend using a proper screen recorder for this task, you are welcome to explore this VLC feature for fun.</strong></p><h2 id="screen-recording-with-vlc"> Screen recording with VLC</h2><div class="kg-card kg-callout-card kg-callout-card-red"><div class="kg-callout-emoji"> 🚧</div><div class="kg-callout-text"> While I was able to use VLC for recording desktop screen, I could not record any sound and my mouse cursor. In my opinion, it&#39;s not a replacement of a proper screen recording tool.</div></div><p> To record your screen using <a href="https://www.videolan.org/vlc/?ref=itsfoss.com">VLC</a> , open it and click on Media and select Convert/Save. (Or directly click on Media → Open Capture Device) </p><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption"><img src="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/click-on-convert-save.png" class="kg-image" alt="How to Record Your Screen with VLC [For Fun]" loading="lazy" width="979" height="511" srcset="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/size/w600/2023/09/click-on-convert-save.png 600w, https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/click-on-convert-save.png 979w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px"><figcaption> <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Select Convert/ Save option</span></figcaption></figure><p> Go to the &quot;Capture Device&quot; Tab and select Desktop from the Capture Mode dropdown list. </p><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption"><img src="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/desktop-in-capture-device.png" class="kg-image" alt="How to Record Your Screen with VLC [For Fun]" loading="lazy" width="929" height="482" srcset="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/size/w600/2023/09/desktop-in-capture-device.png 600w, https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/desktop-in-capture-device.png 929w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px"><figcaption> <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Capture Mode: Desktop</span></figcaption></figure><p> Now, provide some frame rate for your recording. 10, 24 fps etc will be good, and if you need more quality, go for higher. Note that this will increase the file size and system requirements. Then, press the Convert/Save button. </p><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption"><img src="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/set-frame-rate-and-press-convert.png" class="kg-image" alt="How to Record Your Screen with VLC [For Fun]" loading="lazy" width="923" height="483" srcset="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/size/w600/2023/09/set-frame-rate-and-press-convert.png 600w, https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/set-frame-rate-and-press-convert.png 923w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px"><figcaption> <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Set Frame Rate</span></figcaption></figure><p> On the next page, select a profile from the drop-down and click on the adjacent button to edit the profile. </p><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption"><img src="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/Select-profile-and-edit.png" class="kg-image" alt="How to Record Your Screen with VLC [For Fun]" loading="lazy" width="887" height="518" srcset="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/size/w600/2023/09/Select-profile-and-edit.png 600w, https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/Select-profile-and-edit.png 887w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px"><figcaption> <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Set Output Profile</span></figcaption></figure><p> Set the Video format you need and press Save. </p><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption"><img src="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/profile-settings.png" class="kg-image" alt="How to Record Your Screen with VLC [For Fun]" loading="lazy" width="1158" height="519" srcset="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/size/w600/2023/09/profile-settings.png 600w, https://itsfoss.com/content/images/size/w1000/2023/09/profile-settings.png 1000w, https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/profile-settings.png 1158w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px"><figcaption> <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Edit the Output Profile</span></figcaption></figure><p> Now, you need to give a destination file name. Click on the Browse button, select a location, and enter the name of the output file. Click Save. </p><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption"><img src="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/give-name-to-output-file-and-save.png" class="kg-image" alt="How to Record Your Screen with VLC [For Fun]" loading="lazy" width="1103" height="523" srcset="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/size/w600/2023/09/give-name-to-output-file-and-save.png 600w, https://itsfoss.com/content/images/size/w1000/2023/09/give-name-to-output-file-and-save.png 1000w, https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/give-name-to-output-file-and-save.png 1103w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px"><figcaption> <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Output file location and Name</span></figcaption></figure><p> Press the Start button, to start recording your screen. </p><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption"><img src="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/press-start-button-to-start-recrding.png" class="kg-image" alt="How to Record Your Screen with VLC [For Fun]" loading="lazy" width="1100" height="517" srcset="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/size/w600/2023/09/press-start-button-to-start-recrding.png 600w, https://itsfoss.com/content/images/size/w1000/2023/09/press-start-button-to-start-recrding.png 1000w, https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/press-start-button-to-start-recrding.png 1100w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px"><figcaption> <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Start Recording</span></figcaption></figure><p> This will start recording. Once you finished your recording, use the panel button to stop. </p><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption"><img src="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/stop-button-in-panel-1.png" class="kg-image" alt="How to Record Your Screen with VLC [For Fun]" loading="lazy" width="904" height="628" srcset="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/size/w600/2023/09/stop-button-in-panel-1.png 600w, https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/stop-button-in-panel-1.png 904w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px"><figcaption> <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Stop Recording</span></figcaption></figure><p> Or click on the stop button on VLC. </p><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption"><img src="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/Stop-button-in-VLC.png" class="kg-image" alt="How to Record Your Screen with VLC [For Fun]" loading="lazy" width="938" height="536" srcset="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/size/w600/2023/09/Stop-button-in-VLC.png 600w, https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/Stop-button-in-VLC.png 938w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px"><figcaption> <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Stop Button in VLC</span></figcaption></figure><p>就是这样。 You can view the screen recording on the place where you saved it. </p><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption"><img src="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/recorded-output.png" class="kg-image" alt="How to Record Your Screen with VLC [For Fun]" loading="lazy" width="1125" height="464" srcset="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/size/w600/2023/09/recorded-output.png 600w, https://itsfoss.com/content/images/size/w1000/2023/09/recorded-output.png 1000w, https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/09/recorded-output.png 1125w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px"><figcaption> <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Output File</span></figcaption></figure><h2 id="conclusion">结论</h2><p>As you can see, while it is possible to record the desktop screen with VLC, it is not a replacement of a <a href="https://itsfoss.com/best-linux-screen-recorders/">dedicated screen recording tool</a> . Lack of audio recording is a major letdown.</p><figure class="kg-card kg-bookmark-card"> <a class="kg-bookmark-container" href="https://itsfoss.com/best-linux-screen-recorders/"><div class="kg-bookmark-content"><div class="kg-bookmark-title">10 Best Screen Recorders for Linux in 2023</div> <div class="kg-bookmark-description">Take a look at the best screen recorders available for Linux. Learn its key features, pros, and cons.</div> <div class="kg-bookmark-metadata"><img class="kg-bookmark-icon" src="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/size/w256h256/2022/12/android-chrome-192x192.png" alt="How to Record Your Screen with VLC [For Fun]"> <span class="kg-bookmark-author">It&#39;s FOSS</span> <span class="kg-bookmark-publisher">Munif Tanjim</span></div></div> <div class="kg-bookmark-thumbnail"><img src="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/08/best-screen-recorders.png" alt="How to Record Your Screen with VLC [For Fun]"></div></a></figure><p> Use VLC for screen recording only if you don&#39;t have any other options.你怎么认为？</p> ;
